\cf2\b MiniPlayer\cf0\b0\par
The MiniPlayer is a compact, always\f2\_on\_top version of Skye\f1\lang1033  \f2\lang9 Music designed for quick access, clean visuals, and minimal screen footprint. It gives you the essential\f1\lang1033 s: \f2\lang9 playback controls, \f1\lang1033 album art, \f2\lang9 track information, and a visualizer\f1\lang1033 , \f2\lang9 while staying out of your way.\f1\lang1033  \f2\lang9 The MiniPlayer is designed to keep Skye\f1\lang1033  \f2\lang9 Music visible while you work, browse, or game, offering a lightweight way to enjoy visualizers without opening the full window. It can be tucked neatly into a corner of your screen, making it perfect as a small \ldblquote desk companion\rdblquote  version of the app that stays out of the way while still giving you quick access to playback and visuals. The MiniPlayer is intentionally simple\f1\lang1033  \f2\lang9 and unobtrusive.\par
\par
You can open the MiniPlayer from the main player\rquote s menu, from the tray icon by\b  \f1\lang1033 <D\f2\lang9 ouble\_\f1\lang1033 C\f2\lang9 lick\f1\lang1033 >\b0\f2\lang9 ing it, or by using the keyboard shortcut \b\f1\lang1033 <\f2\lang9 P\f1\lang1033 >\b0\f2\lang9 . \b\f1\lang1033 <ESC> \b0 or \b <P> \b0 will close the MiniPlayer and reopen the Player. \f2\lang9 Closing the MiniPlayer never stops playback; it simply hides the compact view and hands control back to the main window, letting your music continue uninterrupted.\par
\par
Each visualizer offers an \f1\lang1033 "\f2\lang9 Allow MiniMode\f1\lang1033 "\f2\lang9  setting; when enabled, the MiniPlayer uses a version of the visualizer specifically optimized for small spaces, and when disabled, it displays the full visualizer exactly as it appears in the main window\f1\lang1033 , just in a smaller space.\par
